bug.short_desc: kernel 4.9.6-200 panic short after boot in pcie_aspm_init_link_state
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1247255 screenshot of kernel panic
Description of problem: while 4.9.5-200 is booting well, 4.9.6 crashes
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kernel-4.9.6-200.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. update kernel 2. boot
Actual results: panic, last line pcie_aspm_init_link_state
Expected results: booting well
Additional info: see attached screenshot
This looks to be fixed by https://patchwork.kernel.org/patch/9545603/ . I had another build failure with 4.9.7 so I'm going to pull in the patch into that build.
